------------------------------------------------------------
A promise is a tool that is for managing async code flow throught our application.
------------------------------------------------------------
If you want to run something at some point of time then we have to use promises.
------------------------------------------------------------
Promise((resolve, rejected))
------------------------------------------------------------
3 states of Promises :
unresolved 
resolved
rejected
------
unresolved : waiting for something to finish
resolved : something finished and it all went OK
rejected : something finished and something went bad
------------------------------------------------------------
Mongoose is  a library that we are going to use to get a nice and eligent API to work with mongo.
------------------------------------------------------------
npm install --save mocha nodemon mongoose
